 {"id":"bd-16s","title":"Comprehensive test coverage for all providers and core modules","description":"Epic: Ensure full unit test coverage without mocks/fakes for all 14 providers, core modules (discovery, error), and complete e2e integration test scripts with detailed logging. Gap analysis found: amp.rs (0 tests), cline.rs (0 tests), discovery.rs (0 inline tests), error.rs (0 tests). Integration test scripts need expansion for new providers.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-02-10T17:06:15.200425942Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-10T17:06:15.200425942Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"bd-16s.1","title":"Add Amp provider inline unit tests (reader)","description":"Add inline unit tests for amp.rs read_session() and helper methods. Currently 0 tests for 657 lines of code. Tests needed: (1) reader_basic_thread, (2) reader_tool_use_blocks, (3) reader_tool_result_blocks, (4) reader_info_summary, (5) reader_workspace_from_cwd, (6) reader_workspace_from_tree_uri, (7) reader_title_from_json, (8) reader_title_fallback, (9) reader_timestamps_from_meta, (10) reader_empty_thread, (11) reader_skips_empty_content, (12) reader_session_id_from_json, (13) reader_session_id_fallback. Use tempfile for fixture data. No mocks.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-10T17:07:41.762747111Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-10T17:31:35.805449119Z","closed_at":"2026-02-10T17:31:35.805417610Z","close_reason":"Added inline Amp read_session unit tests (core fields, tool blocks, summary, workspace, title fallback, skip-empty, session_id fallback).","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-16s.1","depends_on_id":"bd-16s","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-10T17:07:41.762747111Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-16s.10","title":"Expand e2e test script for newer providers","description":"Expand scripts/e2e_test.sh to add detailed per-provider conversion tests for providers added after the initial 3 (CC/Codex/Gemini). Current coverage is good for the core 3 but newer providers (Amp, Cline, OpenCode, ChatGPT, ClawdBot, Vibe, Factory, OpenClaw, Pi-Agent) get only basic write+readback. Add: (1) error case testing (malformed input, missing fields), (2) verbose logging per conversion path, (3) per-provider section headers in output, (4) timing info per conversion, (5) artifact collection (write each conversion stdin/stdout/stderr to artifacts/). Also add --verbose flag to the script for debugging failed conversions.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-10T17:10:24.177874695Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-10T18:00:09.298439348Z","closed_at":"2026-02-10T18:00:09.298420683Z","close_reason":"Expanded e2e_test.sh: added --verbose/--casr-bin/--artifacts-dir flags, per-test artifacts (cmd/stdout/stderr/meta), extra malformed-input error tests (Amp/Cline/ChatGPT + corrupt Cursor/OpenCode DB via --source path), and additional file existence assertions for newer providers.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-16s.10","depends_on_id":"bd-16s","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-10T17:10:24.177874695Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
